                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13092766" author="kristwaa" created="Mon, 29 Aug 2011 12:13:24 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching patch 1a, which makes the XAMemTest be executed last in the low-mem suite.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve observed a runtime of 46 and 22 minutes for the low-mem suite. It now dropped (back) to around 12 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk with revision 1162737.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103517" author="kristwaa" created="Tue, 13 Sep 2011 11:35:23 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Merged fix to the 10.8 branch, hoping there will be another RC.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t plan to do more on this issue now, but for later, and maybe for similar cases, it should be investigated if using a decorator that shuts down the database (and possibly then engine?) addresses the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13129545" author="kristwaa" created="Tue, 18 Oct 2011 07:44:52 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing issue, no issues seen after the fix was applied.&lt;br/&gt;
The fix committed under this issue was a work-around, not a proper fix addressing the general root cause.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
